data.title: Blade Pitch: Propeller
data.meta_description: 2 - Free download as Word Doc (.doc / .docx), PDF File (.pdf), Text File (.txt) or read online for free. Constant speed propellers can change the angle of attack of the blades to take a smaller or larger "bite" of air as it rotates. A shallower angle of attack requires the least horsepower, but the highest RPM because the propeller is not moving very much air with each revolution. The first constant-speed propellers were counterweight propellers driven by mechanisms which operated on centrifugal force.
